Package gov.nasa.gsfc.spdf.ssc

Class KmlFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nasa.gsfc.spdf.ssc.KmlFactory
  • public class KmlFactory
extends java.lang.Object
    This class produces a Keyhole Markup Language (KML) JAXB representation of SSC satellite location information.

    B. Harris

        public static void addCommentAndSerialize​(jakarta.xml.bind.JAXBContext jaxbContext,

                                          javax.xml.transform.TransformerException
        Adds the given comment to the given JAXB DOM object and then serializes the DOM to the given result stream.
        Parameters:
        jaxbContext - the JAXBContext associated with the given kmlDom.
        kmlDom - the KML JAXB DOM object to serialize.
        comment - the comment to add to kmlDom before serializing.
        result - stream to which kmlDom is to be serialized.
        Throws:
        javax.xml.parsers.ParserConfigurationException - if a ParserConfigurationException occurs.
        jakarta.xml.bind.JAXBException - if a JAXBException occurs.
        javax.xml.transform.TransformerException - if a TransformerException occurs.

      • main

        public static void main​(java.lang.String[] args)
                 throws java.lang.Exception
        Class tester.
        Parameters:
        args - command line arguments. args[0] = name of file containing the SSC location output. The file should be created by specifying the following at SSC Locator:
        • Spacecraft and time range
        • Output Options
          • GEO LAT/LON
          • Radial Distance
          • GEO North B-Field Trace Footpoint Lat/Lon
          • GEO South B-Field Trace Footpoint Lat/Lon
        • Output Format and Units Options
          • Distance = km - Kilometers
          • Direction = Lat (-90,+90), Lon (-180,+180)
          • Output Format Options = CDF
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - if any exception occurs.
